ext_ar":"اَنَسِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is said to be of no account. (TA.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left"},{"kind":"text","text":"side (AZ, S, M, Msb, K) of an animal, (Msb,) or of a beast and of a man, (M,) or of anything: (AZ, S, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right"},{"kind":"text","text":"side: (As, S:) [but the latter seems to be a mistake:] Az says that Lth has well explained this term and its contrary"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$iY~N","text_ar":"وَحْشِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", saying that the latter is the right side of every beast; and the former, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left"},{"kind":"text","text":"side; agreeably with those of the first authority in sound learning; and [that] it is related of El-Mufaddal and As and AO, that all of them asserted the latter to be, of every animal except man, [the “far” side, or “off” side,] the side on which it is not milked nor mounted; and the former, [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near"},{"kind":"text","text":"side,] the side"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on which the rider mounts and the milker milks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."}],"source_refs":["S","K","AZ","M","Msb","As"]}]}}